VThere's a man out there, somewhere,
p4
aVwho looks a little bit like the actor Idris Elba,
p5
aVor at least he did 20 years ago.
p6
aVI don't know anything else about him,
p7
aVexcept that he once saved my life
p8
aVby putting his own life in danger.
p9
aVThis man ran across four lanes of freeway traffic in the middle of the night
p10
aVto bring me back to safety
p11
aVafter a car accident that could have killed me.
p12
aVAnd the whole thing left me really shaken up, obviously,
p13
aVbut it also left me with this kind of burning, gnawing need
p14
aVto understand why he did it,
p15
aVwhat forces within him caused him to make the choice
p16
aVthat I owe my life to,
p17
aVto risk his own life to save the life of a stranger?
p18
aVIn other words, what are the causes of his or anybody else's capacity for altruism?
p19
aa(lp20
VBut first let me tell you what happened.
p21
aVThat night, I was 19 years old
p22
aVand driving back to my home in Tacoma, Washington,
p23
aVdown the Interstate 5 freeway,
p24
aVwhen a little dog darted out in front of my car.
p25
aVAnd I did exactly what you're not supposed to do,
p26
aVwhich is swerve to avoid it.
p27
aVAnd I discovered why you're not supposed to do that.
p28
aVI hit the dog anyways,
p29
aVand that sent the car into a fishtail,
p30
aVand then a spin across the freeway,
p31
aVuntil finally it wound up in the fast lane of the freeway
p32
aVfaced backwards into oncoming traffic
p33
aVand then the engine died.
p34
aVAnd I was sure in that moment that I was about to die too,
p35
aVbut I didn't
p36
aVbecause of the actions of that one brave man
p37
aVwho must have made the decision
p38
aVwithin a fraction of a second of seeing my stranded car
p39
aVto pull over and run across four lanes of freeway traffic
p40
aVin the dark
p41
aVto save my life.
p42
aVAnd then after he got my car working again
p43
aVand got me back to safety and made sure I was going to be all right,
p44
aVhe drove off again.
p45
aVHe never even told me his name,
p46
aVand I'm pretty sure I forgot to say thank you.
p47
aa(lp48
VSo before I go any further,
p49
aVI really want to take a moment
p50
aVto stop and say thank you to that stranger.
